title: France in the Nineteenth Century
creator: Elizabeth Wormeley Latimer
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of France in the Nineteenth Century, by Elizabeth Wormeley Latimer. Read by Cathy Barratt. Author Elizabeth Latimer synthesizes notes from a variety of sources to produce this summary of the nation of France in the 19th century. (Summary by Cathy Barratt) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
